In 1838 Morse successfully demonstrated his achievement before Congress in 1838 but he struggled to make his system work over long distances. At this time there were no power plants so it was quite difficult to maintain the electrical charge. In 1844 Morse succeeded in sending a message “What hath God wrought” from the Supreme Court to Baltimore a distance of 35 miles. The telegraph caught on very quickly. Great Britain and France were joined by the telegraph in 1851 and Great Britain and the United States in 1858.

Morse seeing the opportunity decided to work on using electric current to improve this system. Morse researched the works of others and found that Joseph Henry had worked out a system that used electric current to ring a bell a mile away. Morse's contribution was to devise a distinctive alphabet of electrical pulses that appeared as dots and dashes that could be sent over wire cables and then converted into English.

He gave up art after being passed over paint the new capital building in Washington. In his grief he turned to other pursuits namely perfecting a communication system he observed in France. The semaphore  system brought news to Paris from France’s ports. When ships came in a set of towers outfitted with flags and mechanical moving arms relayed the messages. This system worked amazingly in during the day and in good weather. At night and in bad weather it was hopelessly useless.

This meant that the early rail lines and locomotives were of poor quality so early passengers had to promise to help lift derailed locomotives back on the rail line and help shovel away snow during winter. The travel was so hazardous that when locomotives crashed during the winter it often resulted in fatal fires. This occurred because early locomotives were made of wood. It would not be until the 1890’s that locomotives were completely made of steel.

The early railways were short with trips being from town to town. The Erie Railway which linked New York City with Dunkirk on Lake Erie took 16 years to build being completed in 1851. The company that constructed the line faced a number of hardships from lack of funds, to acquiring land for the rail line, retaining their labor force and finding functioning equipment.

Man must form a clear and definite mental image of the things he wishes to have, to do, or to become; and he must hold this mental image in his thoughts, while being deeply grateful to the Supreme that all his desires are granted to him. The man who wishes to get rich must spend his leisure hours in contemplating his Vision, and in earnest thanksgiving that the reality is being given to him. Too much stress cannot be laid on the importance of frequent contemplation of the mental image, coupled with unwavering faith and devout gratitude. This is the process by which the impression is given to the Formless, and the creative forces set in motion. The creative energy works through the established channels of natural growth, and of the industrial and social order. All that is included in his mental image will surely be brought to the man who follows the instructions given above, and whose faith does not waver. What he wants will come to him through the ways of established trade and commerce.

The Science of Getting Rich, Wallace D. Wattles

Posture = A balancing act. It starts with a strong and stable base ✔️
👣Posture is an overused term and it is affected by many things. A huge part of overall posture is stability and balance from the ground up in order to promote better overall stacking of the ribcage and pelvis (think neutral spine)
👣 Our hips and feet determine how well we can stack our pelvis in a neutral position. If a person cannot use their feet and arches properly, then they are already dealing with an unstable base of support that the rest of the body must try to make up for somehow
👣 Learning how to create an arch and use your feet allows you to create stability from the ground up. Your body loves and craves stability, so working on your foot function is a key way to give it that
🔑 gradually spend more time barefoot, being conscious of your foot position and arch
🔑 gradually train more barefoot
🔑 Single leg balance with your arch formed as much as you can
👣 A key part of posture is your base of support, so get those feet doing what they are supposed to do

The mark 15 nuclear bomb was lost during a practice exercise, when an F-86 fighter plane collided with the B-47 bomber carrying the bomb. To protect the aircrew from a possible detonation in the event of a crash, the bomb was jettisoned. Following several unsuccessful searches, the bomb was presumed lost somewhere in the waters off Tybee Isand, near Savannah, Georgia.
